		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">quexxon wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><ul>-- Chapter 09 - Beyond the Basics (Less common 6502 instructions, More Economic Programming Techniques)<br />-- Chapter 10 - Beyond NROM (Mappers in depth - When is a mapper necessary? Which mapper should you use and how do you use it?)<br /></ul></div><br /><br />I see these as more appendix-like material rather than thrown in the middle, but that's counter to your guiding principle, so I'm just stating it as my opinion.  The first game you strive to create should be basic enough that it doesn't need too many cycle-counting tricks [as you laid out in your general principles], and certainly shouldn't be bigger than 16 or 32KB.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">quexxon wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sidebar: How to set up the work environment required for this book on Linux, Mac, and Windows systems.<br /></div>
